<p sourcefile="security/authorization/views.md" sourcestartlinenumber="53" sourceendlinenumber="53">Here you can see the model is passed as the resource authorization should take into consideration.</p>
<div class="WARNING" sourcefile="security/authorization/views.md" sourcestartlinenumber="55" sourceendlinenumber="55"><h5>Warning</h5><p sourcefile="security/authorization/views.md" sourcestartlinenumber="56" sourceendlinenumber="56">Do not rely on showing or hiding parts of your UI as your only authorization method. Hiding a UI element does not mean a user cannot access it. You must also authorize the user within your controller code.</p>
